sql:
SELECT models.model_name, teams.team_name
FROM models
INNER JOIN teams ON models.team_id = teams.team_id;

SELECT u.user_name, t.team_name
FROM users u
JOIN teams t ON u.team_id = t.team_id;

external_knowledge:
- "shining star" metaphorically refers to a model that excels among others; 
- "crossed the 90% accuracy threshold" refers to the condition that the classification accuracy must be greater than 90%;
- "illustrating its brilliance by standing out" suggests the model's exceptional performance;
- "standing out in the vast sky of machine learning models" metaphorically describes the uniqueness of the model among numerous others.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT algorithm 
FROM models 
WHERE team_id = 1;

SELECT model_name 
FROM models 
WHERE training_time = (SELECT MAX(training_time) FROM models);
